        {
          "type": "missing_content",
          "description": "The English text 'Sort by' implies a prepositional relationship or a label for a selection, whereas the Korean '정렬' (Sort) is a noun/verb meaning just 'Sorting'. While often used, it misses the 'by' nuance which in UI context often precedes the criteria. However, more critically, in many UI patterns, 'Sort by' is translated as '정렬 기준' (Sort criteria) to be grammatically complete for a label.",
